## Validation Sequence (before opening any PRs)

```
1. PR 1 branch only, all clients on release branches  →  build must pass
2. PR 1 branch + all PR 2* feature branches           →  build must pass
3. PR 3 branch + all PR 2* feature branches           →  build must pass
```

Only after step 3 passes do you open PRs, in dependency order:
- Open PR 1 first.
- Open PR 2a/2b/2c in parallel (they only depend on PR 1 being merged).
- Open PR 3 last (depends on PR 1 + all PR 2* merged).

**Before pushing any branch and opening a PR, always rebase it onto the current
tip of the target branch (`release/MAPL-v3` or equivalent):**

```bash
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/release/MAPL-v3
git push -u origin <branch>   # or --force-with-lease if already pushed
```

This ensures CI runs against the latest code and avoids unnecessary merge
conflicts after approval.

