## Useful Grep Commands

```bash
# Find all files using a legacy module
grep -rn "use NCIOMod\|use FileIOSharedMod\|use MAPL_LocStreamMod" \
  src/ --include="*.F90" --include="*.f90"

# Find all files using MAPL2
grep -rn "use MAPL2" src/ --include="*.F90" --include="*.f90"

# Check what symbols a file actually uses from a module
grep -A2 "use MAPL2" path/to/file.F90

# Find C companion files for a Fortran module
grep -n "bind(C\|c_\|_F\.c" base/SOME_MOD.F90
```
